OL,5,Cdonor
OL,7,FThe Labour leader began Prime
OL,8,FMinister's Questions by asking the
OL,9,Fprime minister if he was "proud to be
OL,10,Fbankrolled by someone using racist and
OL,11,Fmisogynist language?".
OL,13,FMr Sunak replied saying "the alleged
OL,14,Fcomments were wrong, they are racist,
OL,15,Fhe has rightly apologised for them and
OL,16,Fthat should be accepted".
OL,18,FThe Tory donor said he is "deeply
OL,19,Fsorry" for being "rude" to Ms Abbott,
OL,20,Fbut has not apologised for being
OL,21,F"racist".
