OL,7,FGovernment ministers Mel Stride and
OL,8,FGraham Stuart enforced the government
OL,9,Fposition on Tuesday that the comments
OL,10,Fwere "unacceptable" but not "racist".
OL,12,FMr Stride said it wasn't a "race-based
OL,13,Fcomment", and Mr Stuart said he was
OL,14,F"not ready to put a label" on the
OL,15,Fcomments.
OL,17,FMr Stuart also said the Tory donor
OL,18,Fshouldn't be cancelled because of what
OL,19,Fhe said - "Do we have to destroy this
OL,20,Fman because he said these unacceptable
OL,21,Fthings? I would hope not", he said.
